S:log-item.D:comment: checking in fixes to allow a 50 user by 59 minute configuration of the stress test to be run. I ran this once so far on a 4 way, XP box and it passed. In the past this test has sometimes found bugs that the shorter and less users stress test did not uncover - I seem to remember it mostly being useful for statement cache issues. Note on my machine each run eats up around 11 gig - mostly from the .out files of each of the test runners.
